	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, my friend is a lvl 54 mage (damn, that makes me so jeallous ;)<BR>
<BR>
I'm not sure on what lvl Warriors were, but they were NOT lvl 60, but I do know they were at least lvl 45. Don't worry, I love my class, but I'm not so hard headed to say an epic mage pet can take on 4 lvl 60 Warriors ;)<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, look at it. Do a who all Warrior and ask a lvl 55+ War what weapon he has. I GUARANTEE they duel wield (no one goes for the 2 handers). Now what is the problem with that?? Well, if you're duel wielding you're obviously going to get FAST weapons, that aren't as powerful as 2 handers. Most of them will have weapons like Frostbringers, etc. Now what you'd do is...<BR>
<BR>
BOIV pet<BR>
Wait for pet to DS himself<BR>
<BR>
And what you'd see is...<BR>
<BR>
Soandso hits Jobober for 45 points of damage<BR>
Soandso was burned (for 50 damage)<BR>
Soandso hits Jobober for 45 points of damage<BR>
Soandso was burned (for 50 damage)<BR>
Soandso hits Jobober for 45 points of damage<BR>
Soandso was burned (for 50 damage)<BR>
Soandso hits Jobober for 45 points of damage<BR>
Soandso was burned (for 50 damage)<BR>
Jobober hits Soandso for 67 points of damage<BR>
Jobober hits Soandso for 67 points of damage<BR>
Jobober hits Soandso for 67 points of damage<BR>
Jobober hits Soandso for 67 points of damage<BR>
Jobober bashes Soandso for 26 points of damage<BR>
Jobeber stuns Soandso<BR>
Jobober nukes Soandso for 200 points of damage<BR>
<BR>
And while other warriors hit pet they WILL be burned for 50. They're killing themselves, plain and simple.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, mage epic pet is very very powerful, no need to tell you that. But don't take my word for it. See if for yourself, and believe me, you will. You'll eventually get to go on plane raids. Just make sure you on the group of the mage that has epic and watch your group get most (if not all) the kills.<BR>
<BR>
About the whole deal with dueling Necros/Chanter/SKs...<BR>
<BR>
&lt;&lt;Best duelers? Sorry bro, but you don't realize a few things. You say you have uber resist, but what if the other classes them also?&gt;&gt;<BR>
<BR>
Like I said, you DO NOT need to nuke them AT ALL. Pet will do the job. Your lvl 49 fire/air pet will LITERALLY DESTROY a wizard in SECONDS. Get a watch and time yourself. All you have to do is keep Dispelling pet. That is all. Wizards CANNOT touch you in any way if you have resist over 90 or so, and mine's just over 130. Buffing myself I can get it up to 160 I think (Shielding/Elemental Shielding series).<BR>
<BR>
&lt;&lt;First is that only very stupid duelers don't go for the mage right off the bat. Second is while we can make ourselves immune to spells, we can't do this to our pets.&gt;&gt;<BR>
<BR>
True, but not entirely. You'd be surprised how many stupid duelers are out there.<BR>
<BR>
&lt;&lt;Third is the simple fact that our pets are stupid, sks and necros can lead them far out and fd while their pets pound our ass off(and we mages don't have anyway to deal with this).&gt;&gt;<BR>
<BR>
Not entirelly true. 1. I'm not really sure on this (so don't quote me), but I'm pretty sure FD at those lvls don't work too well. 2. Mages can make their pets IMMUNE to fear. That's all you need to do to your pet. 3. Don't EVER let your pet get away from you. Again, if the Necro is smart, he WILL shadowstep to try to lead pet away, HOWEVER you will not do that because you too are not stupid. Learn to use /pet back off. Love to use /pet back off. Live /pet back off. As soon as Necro shadowsteps, keep pressing that /pet back off key. Another thing is that if the Necro has a pet, YOU WILL NOT sic your pet on the Necro, you will sic your pet on the Necro's pet and watch the Necro's pet die. Have your fire pet tank against the Necro's pet for 5 seconds. That's all you need. 5 Seconds, and cast your lvl 56 EXILE SUMMONED. One dead Necro pet. No arguing. There's no way in hell the Necro pet will leave, or you can go for the kill and use your lvl 60 BANISH SUMMONED, which, as you probably guessed it, BANISHES the Necro's pet. You know what to do after that.<BR>
<BR>
And trust me, I know Necro's very well. It takes about 1/4 to 1/5 of the Necro's mana to summon a pet. And all of their spells take a very, very long time to cast and lots and lots of mana. After his pet is killed and he can't Fear your pet, there is nothing he can do to your pet. Your pet will MURDER a Necro in seconds. Again, get a watch and time it.<BR>
<BR>
Are mages THE best duelers in the game?? No, by all means no. Are they one of the best?? Yes, definetly, and they CAN be the best dueler in game if you know what you're doing. And luck is always a good thing to have on your side.<BR>
<BR>
Ask anyone who the best duelers are. They'll say...<BR>
<BR>
Necro<BR>
Chanter<BR>
Shadow Knight<BR>
<BR>
Am I right or wrong?? You know that. You've heard people saying that.<BR>
<BR>
But trust me, with the right equip, they cannot touch you in any way.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck to you all and duel duel duel!!! Become a master at it. Believe me, at later lvls dueling will be the only thing that will actually give you pleasure in the game. It's fun and it'll be your life.<BR>
<BR>
It's a game people. PLAY with it. Do things you've never done before. Challenge a class to a duel that you've never dueled with. Watch their tactics, learn their tactics, know how to counter their tactics.<BR>
<BR>
Know what THE best dueling class in game is IMHO?? <BR>
<BR>
Bards<BR>
<BR>
Now there's a REAL challenge ;)
				</font>
			</td>

