			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ahem... anyway, getting back to the topic.<BR>
<BR>
Erudites are much better int casters. Face it everyone. I know it, you know, they all know it. <BR>
<BR>
You n00bies probably don't hang out with high lvls very much (and I'm talking about 55+. Look me up, Arkanus on E'Ci, lvl 60 Arch Mage).<BR>
<BR>
Ask ANY int casters that didn't pick an Erudite. Now ask them what other race they would like to be. Yes, you got it. About 70% of them will say Erudite. Why?? Because once you max out your int (which is very very easy being an Erudite), then you can raise the BEST stats on the game. SAVES (and maybe AC). You got a high int, then you can get saves, and then you will be UNBEATABLE. With high saves you can fight against Necros, Chanter, SKs, etc, and they won't even be able to touch you. With the right equip the mage is THE best dueler class in the game. Nuff said, deal with it. Do your own research if you must.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;I would trade my int for a few more hp&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Dude, what kinda statement is that?? You're a FRIGGING MAGE!!!! Mages have low hit points!!! If you want more hit points, then why the *** did you start a mage?? Really. Stop making those stupid comments, cuz let me tell you right now, you make one of those in the game and you will be black listed for life.<BR>
<BR>
And plus, Erudites have the best stamina in the game (for any classes that can be a mage that is), so if you choose an Erudite, YOU WILL have more stamina then every other caster. I'm lvl 60 and I have about 120 of stamina. About 20 more stamina then a guildmate of mine who is a HUMAN WARRIOR. Yes, I have more stamina than a warrior. I have ALL MY SAVES OVER 130!!! NOTHING can touch me. NOTHING. I can fight a Chanter (who is considered to be THE best duelist class in the game), and even after then Tashani me, their spells CANNOT hit me. I can fight Necros, and their spells won't work on me. And even worse, they don't have a debuffer. The can't land a single spell on me. Same for Wizards and SKs.<BR>
<BR>
Just last week I took on 3 wizards at once!!! Yes, at once. Yes, I could hardly hit them too, but I didn't have to, my pet would do most of the work. My pet would lay waste to a wizard in literally 20 seconds or less.<BR>
<BR>
Deal with it. Mages a frigging gods WITH the right equip.<BR>
<BR>
So quit yer damn whinning, cuz believe me, YOU DO NOT want to trade your int for AC and HP... at least not yet.<BR>
<BR>
All I have to say is stick with your class till the end. I don't have to tell you that. You probably know it already if you're beyond lvl 16. Mages are one of the best soloers out there (if not THE best). I lvl up up to 4 times faster than my guild mates. I am a lvl 60 and I have about 35 days on my char. Ask any other class and I guarantee you they will have it AT LEAST 60+ on their characters.<BR>
<BR>
And I'm not even gonna get started on the epic. Once, and if, you get the epic then you will a mage's true power. I do not have my epic yet (but am working on it), but my friend's epic with FS can take on 4 WARRIORS AT ONCE!!! Believe, you do not want to be up against a mage and his pet, specially if the mage knows what he's doing, has the right equip, and even worse for the other class if the mage has the epic.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, Erudites are a better choice, no doubt about it, but that doesn't mean other classes are worthless (well, I would have to say that about Humans). They're not good at anything. The truly suck in my opinion.<BR>
<BR>
And about the whole blindess thing. DEAL WITH IT. At lvl 29 you'll get Summon Coldstone, and believe me, you will be using that all the way up to 60. So the whole blindess thing is pure bullshiet. Don't even try to talk about that with me.<BR>
<BR>
What do you want?? BEST int in game, HIGH AC, HIGH sta, VERY HIGH SAVES or just being able to see perfectly well at night till you're lvl 29???<BR>
<BR>
I hope you picked the first choice, or else you might try seeking mental help. It takes less than 10 days to get to lvl 29. Believe me, its well worth it.<BR>
<BR>
Peace out. 
