	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Magician---aka----Mage<BR>
<BR>
For thoses who are smart enough or lucky enough to get this website and do a little reading of the classes before 'rolling' one up---Congrads.<BR>
<BR>
And a huge hint, out of all the classes to choose from, in my views...do NOT get Mage.<BR>
<BR>
Repeat--do NOT get the mage.  <BR>
<BR>
Mages do not have the massive Nuke-age spells levels as the Wizards do. It basicaly a toned-down version of the Wiz.<BR>
<BR>
Your spell casting ability is depentant on not being attacked by monsters. EI--having a pet take the damages for you or being forever stuck in a group, hoping that they will attack the MOBS while your in the back ground. A hit from a MOB and your sure-fire spell becomes useless.<BR>
 No--you are not casting your 168 hitpoint direct damage fireball that will save you butt-- You just wasted time that could of been spent RUNNING AWAY. Learn this phrase. RUNNING AWAY. Thats what MAGES are good for.  In Combat, Mages by themselves are a fresh meal for the monster or monsters. Be prepared to waste hours of adventuring and wasted exp if you choose this class.<BR>
<BR>
Pets---again--Worthless. In therory, they are your front and last line of attack and defence. Often refered to as 'meat shields'. What they do however, instead of protecting you..they often run off like some darn toy poodle and 'taught' Mr.T, who seeks you out and smashes your face into the ground. Pet do not obey and they always run out of 'hearing range' of your orders, even if you can directly see them. My pets run amok so often that I find the only way to get rid of them, is to go Invisible.<BR>
<BR>
Mages do NOT get all the cool, high earning spells such as SOW--Spirt of the Wolf--or Ports &lt;teleport&gt;.<BR>
<BR>
What are the groups hiring??: Tanks--big,massive TANKS &lt;fighters&gt; and HEALERS &lt;DRUIDS&gt;---oh my god...HEALERS.  What are we NOT hearing being shouted for?? When was the last time you heard a Group BEG for a MAGE?? <BR>
<BR>
At level 21, MAGES can learn the skill--DODGE...a bit fu***ing late, if you ask us. And again ,DODGE often gets you killed instead of working. INVISIBLE does not work to The Undead<BR>
AND after a Monster has attacked your pet, your party or you. INV does NOTHING to help you HIDE after beign jumped---And you will be JUMPED--alot!!<BR>
<BR>
More BS they didnt tell you----after level 16, you have to RESEARCH your more advanced spells--thats right. RESEARCH--spend your hard earn money and time to run around gathering items to be put a combined items--in hopes that it will make a spell--when most of the time, like what feels like 99%, it will fail, wasting everything.<BR>
<BR>
Want to buy ALL your spells? Not gonna happen. Your run to one store---find about 10% of what your looking for--then spend another few hours running clear across the world , to find another 10%.<BR>
<BR>
For all the time and effort placed into this class, you are just better of being a druid. They have all the cool money making spells, can HIDE, and are always wanted and invited into groups.<BR>
<BR>
Mages, as a class---sux---. Maybe one day, EQ will make a patch that gives them thier own SOW version and teleport<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
